                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d659">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/3340: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-12-29T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 29, 1931—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 29—6:17 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1146. The Military Attaché at Chinchow telegraphs that the railway company has
                    been ordered by the Chinese military authorities to assemble 6 locomotives and
                    150 cars at Chinchow, and it is his opinion that the Chinese troops are on the
                    point of withdrawing within the Great Wall.<note n="9" xml:id="d659fn9">For
                        decision to withdraw, see telegram No. 1148, December 29, 1931, 10 a.m.,
                        from the Minister in China, <ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_75">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 75</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Repeated to Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
